Example Gameplay
Below is an example of how the game script runs:
========================================================================================

Welcome to the Number Guessing Game
I'm thinking of a number between 1 and 100. Guess it.

Choose a level of difficulty.
"Easy" or "Hard"?: Easily
Wrong spelling. Type one of ['easy', 'hard']: Easy

You have 10 attempts to guess the number
Make a guess: 50
Too low
Guess again

You have 9 attempts to guess the number
Make a guess: 75
Too high
Guess again

You have 8 attempts to guess the number
Make a guess: 62
Too high
Guess again

You have 7 attempts to guess the number
Make a guess: 56
Too high
Guess again

You have 6 attempts to guess the number
Make a guess: 53
Too high
Guess again

You have 5 attempts to guess the number
Make a guess: 52
Congrats! You guessed correctly the number 52

End of the game. You are a winner
-----------------------------------

Do you want to play again? Yes or No? Ok
Wrong spelling. Type one of ['yes', 'no']: yeah
Wrong spelling. Type one of ['yes', 'no']: yes 

Ok, we will start again. Choose a level of difficulty.
"Easy" or "Hard"?: Let's go hard
Wrong spelling. Type one of ['easy', 'hard']: HARD

You have 5 attempts to guess the number
Make a guess: 50
Too low
Guess again

You have 4 attempts to guess the number
Make a guess: 80
Too high
Guess again

You have 3 attempts to guess the number
Make a guess: 63
Too low
Guess again

You have 2 attempts to guess the number
Make a guess: 72
Too low
Guess again

You have 1 attempts to guess the number
Make a guess: 76
Too low
Guess again

End of the game. Unfortunately you lost... The number to guess was 77
-----------------------------------

Do you want to play again? Yes or No? Nah 
Wrong spelling. Type one of ['yes', 'no']: NO

It was nice to play with you! Goodbye
